main event: Three round objects, the size of a car, were observed in a V formation with a luminous trail over Corpus Christi, Texas on 23 October 1957.
interesting points: The sighting lasted between 3 to 5 seconds.,The objects were reported to be traveling in a straight line.,The case was evaluated as a meteor sighting.,The report includes a description conforming to a bolide observation.,There were no unusual radar detections during the sighting.
sighted object: three round luminous objects in a V formation
